%N A394317 Concatenated permutations of integers in decimal.
%C A394317 The terms of the n-th row of the triangle are the n! concatenations of each permutation of 0, ..., n-1.
%C A394317 Starting with row 11, each concatenated term involves at least one number with more than one digit (see example).
%H A394317 Rhys Evans, <a href="/A394317/b394317.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A394317 Rhys Evans, <a href="/A394317/a394317.png">Plot of first 153 terms</a>
%H A394317 Rhys Evans, <a href="/A394317/a394317.ts.txt">Typescript program for OEIS A394317</a>
%e A394317 The triangle starts:
%e A394317 0;
%e A394317 (0)1, 10;
%e A394317 (0)12, (0)21, 102, 120, 201, 210;
%e A394317 ...
%e A394317 Row 11 starts:
%e A394317 (0)12345678910, (0)12345678109, (0)12345679810, ... .
%o A394317 // Typescript (see linked file)
%o A394317 (Python)
%o A394317 from itertools import count, islice, permutations
%o A394317 def a(): yield from (int("".join(map(str, p))) for n in count(1) for p in permutations(range(n)))
%o A394317 print(list(islice(a(), 57))) # _Michael S. Branicky_, Mar 15 2026
%Y A394317 Cf. A030299.
%Y A394317 A precursor of A215940.
